@* _ValidationScriptsPartial.cshtml bundles the jQuery validation scripts. Forms that want
   client-side validation render this (via a Scripts section) so the data-annotation rules on
   the view models (e.g. [Required], [StringLength], [Compare]) are checked in the browser
   before submitting — instant feedback without a round trip. The same rules are ALSO enforced
   server-side, so this is a convenience layer, not the security boundary. *@
<script src="~/lib/jquery-validation/dist/jquery.validate.min.js"></script>
<script src="~/lib/jquery-validation-unobtrusive/dist/jquery.validate.unobtrusive.min.js"></script>
